3) Explanation

It would take 4 moves for the knight to move across the board.
Move 1 would have it move forward 2 of the 8 squares
Move 2 would have it move forward another 2 squares,
At Move 3 the knight would move forward another 2 squares leaving it on the 7th square
Move 4 would be the final move in which the knight moves across 3 squares and forward 1 as it can no longer move forward by one move

